!!【柯林斯英汉双解大词典】

:<div>

examine /ɪɡˈzæmɪn/

(examining,examined,examines) 

1. V-T If you examine something, you look at it carefully. 仔细检查 

例： He examined her passport and stamped it. 他仔细检查了她的护照，然后在上面盖了章。 

2. examination N-VAR 仔细检查 

例： The navy is to carry out an examination of the wreck tomorrow. 海军明天将会对失事船只作仔细检查。 

3. V-T If a doctor examines you, he or she looks at your body, feels it, or does simple tests in order to check how healthy you are. 诊察 

例： Another doctor examined her and could still find nothing wrong. 另一个医生对她进行了检查，仍然找不出任何毛病。 

4. examination N-VAR 诊察 

例： He was later discharged after an examination at the hospital. 后来他在医院做过检查后就出院了。 

5. V-T If an idea, proposal, or plan is examined , it is considered very carefully. 审查 

例： The plans will be examined by officials. 这些计划将由官员们审查。 

6. examination N-VAR 审查 

例： The government said it was studying the implications, which 'required very careful examination and consideration.' 政府称正在对可能的影响进行研究，而这“需要仔细的审查和考虑”。 

7. V-T If you are examined , you are given a formal test in order to show your knowledge of a subject. 考试 [usu passive] 

例： ...learning to cope with the pressures of being judged and examined by our teachers. …学会应付被老师们评价和考试所带来的压力。

